### File Overview
This file defines TestEnterpriseAudit, a Django REST Framework APITestCase test suite exercising the EnterpriseAuditMiddleware behavior by performing API operations (create, update, delete, m2m changes) and asserting the Event audit records and diff formats produced.

### Architecture
- The file imports Django/DRF test utilities, models (Group, User, Event, EventAction), the EnterpriseAuditMiddleware class, and helpers (sanitize_item, generate_id, create_test_admin_user).
- A single test class, TestEnterpriseAudit, subclasses APITestCase and contains multiple test methods. Tests typically:
  - Force-login a test admin user,
  - Perform API requests (user create/patch/delete, group add/remove user),
  - Query the Event model for the audit events produced,
  - Assert that event.context contains the expected "diff" structure or lack thereof.
- Many tests patch EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled (via PropertyMock) to True so the middleware behaves as enabled for assertions.
- One test calls EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.serialize_simple directly to assert behavior when update_fields is provided.

### Functions & Classes
- TestEnterpriseAudit (class) — TestCase grouping all middleware-related tests. Important: central test suite validating how audit diffs are produced for model lifecycle and m2m changes.
  - setUp (method) — Creates and stores a test admin user via create_test_admin_user(). Importance: establishes authentication for API calls in each test.
  - test_import (method) — Ensures that when the authentik_enterprise_audit app's ready() is called, the settings.MIDDLEWARE contains "authentik.enterprise.audit.middleware.EnterpriseAuditMiddleware". It temporarily reverts an import swap, calls apps.get_app_config("authentik_enterprise_audit").ready(), and asserts membership in settings.MIDDLEWARE. Importance: validates bootstrapping/import behavior that ensures the enterprise audit middleware is registered.
  - test_create (method) — With EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled patched True, POSTs to reverse("authentik_api:user-list") to create a new User. It then queries Event objects for action=EventAction.MODEL_CREATED targeting the created user and asserts event.context["diff"] equals a specific dictionary mapping field names to {"new_value": ..., "previous_value": None}. Notable expected diff contents (exact keys and expected formats):
    - "name": {"new_value": user.name, "previous_value": None}
    - "path": {"new_value": "foo", "previous_value": None}
    - "type": {"new_value": "internal", "previous_value": None}
    - "uuid": {"new_value": user.uuid.hex, "previous_value": None}
    - "email": {"new_value": "", "previous_value": None}
    - "username": {"new_value": user.username, "previous_value": None}
    - "is_active": {"new_value": True, "previous_value": None}
    - "attributes": {"new_value": {}, "previous_value": None}
    - "date_joined": {"new_value": sanitize_item(user.date_joined), "previous_value": None}
    - "first_name": {"new_value": "", "previous_value": None}
    - "id": {"new_value": user.pk, "previous_value": None}
    - "last_name": {"new_value": "", "previous_value": None}
    - "password": {"new_value": "********************", "previous_value": None}
    - "password_change_date": {"new_value": sanitize_item(user.password_change_date), "previous_value": None}
    Importance: this test defines the canonical expected diff format for model creation events (every included field maps to new_value/previous_value with previous_value None).
  - test_update (method) — With EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled patched True, creates a user, PATCHes the user via reverse("authentik_api:user-detail") to change the "name" field, then asserts an Event with action=EventAction.MODEL_UPDATED exists and that event.context["diff"] equals:
    - {"name": {"new_value": new_name, "previous_value": current_name}}
    Importance: validates that updates produce a minimal diff containing only changed fields, with both new_value and previous_value present.
  - test_delete (method) — With EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled patched True, creates and deletes a user, asserts an Event with action=EventAction.MODEL_DELETED exists and specifically asserts that "diff" is not present in event.context. Importance: documents expected behavior that deletions should not include a diff in the event context.
  - test_m2m_add (method) — With EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled patched True, creates a user and a Group, POSTs to reverse("authentik_api:group-add-user") to add the user to the group, and asserts an Event with action=EventAction.MODEL_UPDATED for the group exists with:
    - diff == {"users": {"add": [user.pk]}}
    Note: the Event query checks context__model__pk=group.pk.hex (group PK is represented as hex). Importance: defines expected diff format for many-to-many add operations.
  - test_m2m_remove (method) — With EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled patched True, creates a user and a Group, POSTs to reverse("authentik_api:group-remove-user") to remove the user from the group, and asserts an Event with action=EventAction.MODEL_UPDATED for the group exists with:
    - diff == {"users": {"remove": [user.pk]}}
    Importance: defines expected diff format for many-to-many remove operations.
  - test_serialize_fields (method) — With EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled patched True, creates a user and calls EnterpriseAuditMiddleware(None).serialize_simple(user, update_fields=["is_active"]) and asserts the returned state equals {"is_active": True}. Importance: directly asserts the behavior of EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.serialize_simple when update_fields is provided — relevant to how diffs for update fields are serialized.

