The agent is looking for tests that assert behavior around update_fields and audit diffs. Relevant tests and exact expectations:
- test_serialize_fields directly references update_fields by calling EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.serialize_simple(user, update_fields=["is_active"]) and asserting the returned serialization is {"is_active": True}.
- test_update asserts the expected diff format for updates: changed fields must appear as keys with {"new_value": ..., "previous_value": ...} — example for "name".
- test_create asserts the expected canonical diff format for creations: each field is present with {"new_value": ..., "previous_value": None} and includes details such as masked "password", sanitized date fields via sanitize_item, uuid as user.uuid.hex, id as user.pk.
- test_delete asserts deletions should not include a "diff" in the Event context.
- test_m2m_add and test_m2m_remove assert expected diff formats for many-to-many changes:
  - {"users": {"add": [user.pk]}}
  - {"users": {"remove": [user.pk]}}

These tests together define the authoritative expected formats and failure scenarios (e.g., missing diff on delete) your code changes must satisfy or update. The test suite also patches EnterpriseAuditMiddleware.enabled to True — so any behavior gated by that property in the middleware is what these tests enforce.

